stuart symington the nations first air 
force secretary and a us senator from missouri for 24 years died 
wednesday of heart failure he was 87 
symington served in world war i as an army second lieutenant he 
held six various posts within president harry trumans 
administration between 1945 to 1952 including the nations first 
air force secretary from 19471950 
symington served in the us senate from missouri from 1953 to 
1976 deciding at that time not to seek reelection he was a 
favorite son candidate for the democratic presidential 
nomination in 1956 and 1960 symington retired from the senate in 
1976 
