the last five italian warships have left 
the persian gulf in the latest and largest cutback of foreign naval 
forces following the iraniraq ceasefire italian officials say 
the frigate euro flagship of the italian flotilla and the 
minehunters castagno and loto sailed through the strait of hormuz at 
the mouth of the gulf last week the defense ministry in rome said 
wednesday 
they were bound for home 
the frigate sagittario and the supply tanker stromboli left nov 
24 and reached their home port at the taranto naval base in italy on 
monday the ministry said 
italian officials announced the withdrawal in early november 
saying the aug 20 ceasefire which halted fighting in the 
8yearold war had brought a consolidation of stability to the 
strategic waterway 
italy deployed warships in the gulf after the italian container 
ship jolly rubino was attacked by iranian gunboats while sailing to 
kuwait on sept 2 1987 italy kept up to eight ships in the gulf at 
once 
the jolly rubino was the only italianflag vessel among more than 
500 ships attacked by both sides during the fouryear tanker 
war iran regularly intercepted ships suspected of carrying 
warrelated cargoes for iraq during the war 
the italian departure reduced the number of foreign warships in 
or near the gulf to about 50 with half belonging to the united 
states at its peak late last year the foreign naval force 
