<TEXT>
here is a chronology of major events in the history of the 
palestine liberation organization 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 17 arab league summit in cairo establishes plo ahmed 
shukairi palestinian delegate to league later was elected chairman 
of palestine national council which became the plos legislature 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 1 yasser arafat forms fatah guerrilla group 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
june 511 israel captures west bank from jordan gaza strip 
from egypt and syrias golan heights in a sixday war 
nov 22 un security council passes resolution 242 recognizing 
israels right to exist plo rejects the resolution which refers to 
palestinians only as refugees and does not address their claim to 
independent homeland 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
feb 4 palestine national council elects arafat chairman of plo 
executive committee succeeding shukairi 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
september king hussein of jordan alarmed by growing 
palestinian power sends his army to drive guerrillas out of jordan 
arafat moves his base to lebanon series of aircraft hijackings in 
early 1970s cause widespread condemnation of the plo 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
nov 28 black september new palestinian group seeking revenge 
on jordan assassinates wasfi tal jordanian prime minister 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sept 5 black september terrorists seize israeli athletes at 
olympic games in munich and 11 israelis and five palestinians are 
killed 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
april 10 israeli commandos kill three senior plo figures in 
raids on beirut 
oct 6 syria and egypt attack israel 
oct 22 un security council adopts resolution 338 calling 
for implementation of resolution 242 
nov 28 arab league endorses plo as sole legitimate 
representative of palestinian people 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
nov 13 arafat declares in his first speech to un general 
assembly i have come bearing an olive branch and freedom 
fighters gun dont let the olive branch fall from my hand 
nov 22 general asembly recognizes the right of the 
palestinian people to sovereignty and national independence and 
gives the plo observer status at the world organization 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
march 14 israel briefly invades lebanon to destroy guerrilla 
bases 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
june 6 israel invades lebanon for stated purpose of crushing 
plo beginning three years of occupation 
sept 1 plo evacuates beirut and south lebanon 
sept 1517 lebanese christians allied with israel massacres 
hundreds of palestinians and lebanese moslems in beiruts sabra and 
chatilla refugee camps 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
june 24 syria expels arafat after syrianbacked mutiny in 
guerrilla ranks syrian troops later besiege arafat loyalists in 
tripoli north lebanon 
dec 20 arafat withdraws his forces from tripoli last 
stronghold in lebanon 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sept 15 plo guerrillas kill three israelis on hijacked yacht 
at larnaca cyprus 
oct 1 israeli warplanes bomb plo headquarters in tunis 
tunisia in reprisal killing 65 people 
oct 8 proarafat guerrillas hijack italian cruise liner 
achille lauro in the mediterranean and kill leon klinghoffer 
invalid american jew 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
dec 8 palestinians in west bank and gaza strip begin rebellion 
against israeli occupation 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
april 16 israeli commandos assassinate khalil wazir arafats 
deputy in tunis 
nov 15 palestine national council proclaims an independent 
palestinian state and accepts un resolutions 242 and 338 as basis 
for international peace conference 
nov 26 united states refuses arafat a visa to address un 
general assembly in new york assembly later votes to move meeting 
to geneva 
dec 13 arafat addresses session in geneva he renounces 
terrorism and calls for negotiation with israel 
dec 14 president reagan authorizes state department to enter 
into substantive dialogue with plo ending yearslong us 
nonrecognition of the palestinian organization 
