<TEXT>
colorcoded registration stickers soon will 
determine which day of the week private vehicles will be allowed to 
circulate in this smogplagued metropolis 
the plan to issue stickers in five different colors was one of 
several anticontamination measures announced late wednesday by the 
federal government 
officials also said holiday school vacations that began wednesday 
would be extended until february in the city in a bid to cut down 
childrens exposure to healththreatening winter smog 
in addition to the restrictions on private vehicles mexico city 
also will try to battle its critical air pollution problem by 
increasing vehicle inspections prohibiting the burning of tires 
plastics and other contaminating wastes in open areas and setting 
hours for cargo loading and unloading in the city during the smog 
season 
the announcement did not mention sanctions against violators of 
the new regulations generally enforcement of most regulations in 
mexico is lax 
it said that from jan 9 to march 21 vehicles observed to be 
contaminating the air will be taken out of circulation 
beginning jan 16 smog checks will be obligatory for cargo 
vehicles whether they have gas or diesel engines the antiburning 
regulation will be in effect from dec 15 to march 21 
additional measures to reduce air pollution will be announced 
before march 21 according to a bulletin issued by the presidents 
office wednesday night 
city spokesman jose luis manjarrez said officials from the 
federal health education and ecology departments would sign an 
agreement extending the dec 15jan 2 holiday vacation until feb 1 
he said schoolchildren would make up the lost month of classes 
next summer there are about 23 million students in mexico city 
public schools according to federal government statistics 
we have agreed to protect the children of mexico city and part 
of that is to change the school hours manjarrez said we all 
know that the thermal inversion layer levels will be worse during 
the winter and that we have to take measures 
last winter authorities delayed the start of public school 
classes by two hours to limit exposure children often found 
themselves outdoors on the street in the early morning waiting for 
buses while traffic was at its worst and smog at its strongest 
homer aridjis president of the group of 100 a leading 
environmental organization said the schedule change would do little 
to restrict smog exposure schoolage children breathe foul mexico 
city air whether theyre at school or at home he said 
the solution is not to change the school calendar aridjis 
said it is not going to change the pollution situation more 
drastic measures such as less traffic are necessary 
mexico citys smog regularly worsens during winter when a layer 
of warm air traps cold air bearing tons of pollutants near ground 
level the phenomenon is known as a thermal inversion the condition 
can last for hours sometimes days 
the mountains that ring the valley of mexico where mexico city 
lies prevent the dispersal of smog by winds rains are scarce in 
winter permitting winds to lift tons of dust bearing particle 
pollution and dried fecal matter off the dry lake texcoco lakebed 
about 18 million people live in the mexico city metropolitan area 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP881215-0040 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
yasser arafat has come a long way from a 
guerrilla commando force leader to a statesman 
he is the symbol of palestinians desire for a homeland never 
wavering in his dream of creating a palestinian state 
for nearly three decades the 59yearold arafat has been both 
revolutionary chieftain and politician ricocheting between touching 
the dream and losing control of the movement to rivals backed by 
other arab governments 
each setback of the plo chased from jordan in 1970 and from 
lebanon in 1982 was trumpeted as the final demise of arafat each 
time he returned 
and this month he piloted the plo through making the concessions 
demanded by the united states before it would open a dialogue 
israel has denounced him for years as the archterrorist 
masterminding attempts to destroy the jewish state washington just 
last month denied him a visa to address the united nations citing 
his links to terrorism 
but the base of his success has been widespread support among the 
worlds 55 million palestinians in the occupied west bank and gaza 
strip his pictures sprout among demonstrators in the yearold 
uprising against israels 21year occupation 
arafat seems consumed by his mission for a homeland he does not 
smoke or drink and is notorious for latenight meetings 
arafat without wife children or fixed address says he married 
the cause when he formed an underground palestinian movement fatah 
in october 1959 
his date and place of birth have never been confirmed though the 
plo does not dispute the version that he was born aug 29 1929 in 
jerusalems old city 
born mohammed abed arouf arafat his father came from a 
prosperous merchant clan on his mothers side he can trace his 
ancestry back to fatima daughter of the moslem prophet mohammed 
arafat says he smuggled arms to arab forces during the 1948 
arabisraeli war then went to egypt to enroll in cairo university 
in 1952 he was elected president of the palestinian student union 
in egypt 
arafat left egypt in 1957 after taking part in the suez war as a 
reserve officer in the egyptian army he worked in kuwait as a 
government engineer before forming his own successful contracting 
firm 
the plo was created in 1964 and arafat brought fatah above 
ground on jan 1 1965 with its first military commando operation 
against israel 
arafat led commando operations against israel before the 1967 
arabisraeli war later he traveled clandestinely through the west 
bank to organize fatah military units he was elected plo chairman 
in 1969 
in 1970 he faced his first serious challenge from an arab 
government jordans king hussein threatened by the growing power 
of the palestinians within his kingdom moved his army against them 
arafat escaped one of two acknowledged assassination attempts 
that year the second came in october 1971 on an inspection tour in 
syria he says he never sleeps in the same place for two nights 
running 
in 1974 the united nations granted the plo observer status an 
enduring image of arafat is when he addressed the general assembly 
offering an olive branch of peace but wearing an empty holster 
in the late 1970s his guerrillas became embroiled in lebanons 
civil war their strength in southern lebanon led israel to invade 
in 1982 palestinian guerrillas were scattered from tunisia to syria 
after world governments intervened to lift an israeli siege of the 
plo in beirut 
guerrilla leaders disgusted with arafats loyalty to commanders 
who did not stand and fight the israelis got syrian backing to try 
to unseat him arafat was expelled from damascus in june 1983 
proarafat forces were evacuated from tripoli lebanon that 
december 
but arafat moved plo headquarters to tunis and gradually rebuilt 
a consensus among palestinian groups that consensus glued 
together with the uprising in the occupied territories led to this 
months announced change in the palestinian position and the 
projected dialogue with the united states 
arafat and the plo made a political drive in the last month to 
convince the world they are peaceful moderate and worthy of 
representing palestinians in the middle east peace process 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

