a postal employee pulled a shotgun out at the 
main post office wednesday night wounded three people and holed up 
in the building with at least one hostage authorities said 
the gunman eluded police for about five hours before agents found 
him in a room used for coffe breaks during a roomtoroom search of 
the blockwide building said fbi spokesman volney hayes 
the gunman who hayes said was holding at least one hostage 
fired two shots at agents who then backed off 
he was barricaded behind a door as the agents approached he 
fired said cesta ayers a post office spokesman 
negotiations with the gunman were being conducted by telephone 
ayers said early thursday 
earlier hayes said the gunman got into an argument with a 
coworker and pulled a weapon out of a bag 
authorities identified the gunman as warren murphy about 40 a 
sixyear postal worker one of the people shot was the person murphy 
argued with hayes said he did not identify the victim or elaborate 
i was going to mail this box of stuff i have and the security 
guard came down he was real excited said a witness pat 
wingerter of new orleans the guard was screaming theres a guy 
with a gun 
four hours after the incident began at 830 pm authorities 
said an undetermined number of postal employees were apparently 
still inside the building but it was not known if they were being 
held hostage 
about midnight a dozen postal employees who had been laying low 
on the vast second floor escaped through a back door hayes said 
