macys department store to see what was going on 
on aug 20 1986 parttime mailman patrick henry sherrill walked 
into the post office in edmond okla with guns and ammunition 
hidden in his mail bag and began shooting 
he fatally wounded 14 postal workers and injured six others 
before killing himself police thinking sherrill was holding 
workers hostage waited outside for an hour before entering the 
building to aid the wounded and to free employees who had hidden 
from the gunman witnesses said the final shots were heard about 40 
minutes before police entered the building 
