into a substantive dialogue with the palestinian group after 
arafat said he was renouncing all forms of terrorism 
shultz who only two weeks ago barred arafat from entering the 
united states and called him an accessory to terrorism said the 
plo issued a statement in which it met all three us conditions for 
a dialogue the conditions were acceptance of un security council 
resolutions affirming the right of all states to live in peace 
recognition of israel and renunciation of terrorism 
while the israeli government swiftly criticized the move many 
us jewish groups were reluctant to do so reflecting the 
dissension that has marred relations between israel and many 
american jews over israels hardline policies on the west bank and 
gaza strip 
