statement we neither approve nor disapprove we accept it we 
trust the united states 
the first action the us should take in its conversations with 
the plo should be to demand that the plo repeal the palestine 
national covenant which calls for the destruction of the state of 
israel he said 
unless and until the plo translates its words into the deed of 
repealing that covenant there can be no progress toward peace in 
the middle east 
however the simon wiesenthal center in los angeles dedicated to 
the study of the holocaust and promoting israel in world affairs 
said it was disappointed with the decision 
while both president reagan and secretary of state george 
shultz have proven themselves to be the staunchest friends of the 
state of israel the road they have chosen to embark is fraught with 
danger said the statement read by a spokesman rabbi abraham 
cooper 
the response from arabamerican organizations while generally 
favorable was in some cases tinged with bitterness mt mehdi 
