from lhasa that she was reading the book to learn tibetan she said 
police confiscated the book and her passport 
earlier this week authorities barred ms meindersma from leaving 
lhasa but gave her permission to leave wednesday at the request of 
the dutch government 
ms meindersma schwartz and other western witnesses said 
saturdays protest began when about 30 tibetans walked silently into 
lhasas central market square behind a monk carrying the banned flag 
of precommunist tibet 
the witnesses said police opened fire on the crowd without 
warning chinas official media maintains the police gave a warning 
first and then fired in the air 
ms meindersma told the ap she stood not among the demonstrators 
but with a large crowd of curious onlookers she said police 
continued firing at her and others even as they ran from the scene 
in panic 
