the upstairs living quarters and the basement were off limits 
in the living room guests were entertained by violinists and a 
chorus while children lined up to talk to santa and mrs claus 
sandy fiscus who was sampling the refreshments with her 
12yearold daughter robin said they attend the open house every 
year 
the governors chef john decherney and the mansion staff begin 
planning for the threehour affair in july baking begins in 
september and most of the cookies breads and hors doeuvres are 
stored in the freezer 
this year the treats included 1500 egg rolls 1400 artichoke 
pastries 1350 sausage pastries 1400 deviled eggs and 20 pounds 
of brie cheese stuffed with apples and pears by the end only a few 
treats remained 
for many the open house has become a family tradition some 
parents brought video cameras while others took snapshots 
the largest attendance at the open house came in 1983 when an 
estimated 4000 people filed through the mansion interest was 
sparked that year by controversy over a 27 million mansion 
restoration and redecoration project during the term of former gov 
bill sheffield 
the state foots the bill for the open house with expenses coming 
out of the mansion budget cowper spokesman david ramseur said 
