the us agreement to talk with the palestine 
liberation organization spares presidentelect bush one politically 
difficult decision but gives him another arduous task overseeing 
that dialogue 
the decision by the reagan adminstration guarantees that the 
middle easts explosive problems will face bush as soon as he enters 
the oval office on jan 20 even though the vice president said 
thursday theres no game plan theres no fivepoint program 
although initial contacts with the plo are to begin in tunis 
tunisia later this week there is little doubt that the turnabout 
decision clears the way for the bush administration to try to bring 
israel and the palestinians into direct negotiations 
with tensions high on both sides of the 40yearold dispute such 
a task could be monumental 
bush not only will have to deal with plo chairman yasser arafat 
whom just a week before the reagan adminstration had branded a 
terrorist but hell have to do it in a way that avoids souring 
relations with israel 
bush stressed thursday that the initiative which he fully 
supported was a dialogue not negotations 
lets see how things evolve my position remains the same i 
want to see direct talks between for example between king hussein 
of jordan and the israelis he told reporters 
