among chicago and nonchicago health ethnic religious and 
educational groups with bona fide charity status rostenkowski 
doesnt release their names 
weve been running a robin hood program taking from the tax 
lawyers and giving to the poor says the spokesman who declined 
to be quoted by name 
in 1987 225 million of the 98 million in congressional 
honoraria ended up going to charities and nonprofit institutions 
an income source that could dry up if the white house and congress 
accept the pay commissions plan 
rostenkowskis spokesman says the chairman will continue his 
