<TEXT>
a dozen children and teenagers seemed 
to be enjoying themselves thursday rummaging through boxes of 
clothes and toys but the laughter and the smiles vanished as they 
remembered they didnt have a home or parents to return to 
eight days after an earthquake in northwestern armenia sundered 
homes and families officials can only guess at the number of 
children killed or left orphans 
many survivors are having nightmares and the soviet childrens 
fund a charity sent a team of 11 child psychologists to armenia to 
help 
who has trouble sleeping psychologist valeria mukhina asked 
the group of children whose parents are dead or missing 
nearly all raised their hands and yelled i do i do 
the therapy session had begun 
the youngsters from seven to 15 years old were sitting in a 
recital hall of yerevans music conservatory the building was 
converted into a childrens relief center and the hall was filled 
with donated toys and clothes 
