for decades after the communists came to power in 1949 the 
united states recognized their defeated rivals the nationalists on 
taiwan as chinas government ideological suspicion was reinforced 
when the chinese communists and united states found themselves on 
opposite sides in the 195053 korean war 
in 1972 president richard nixon made a dramatic trip to beijing 
and began a process of drawing closer to china that culminated on 
dec 15 1978 when president jimmy carter signed an accord 
recognizing the communist government 
the agreement took effect jan 1 1979 
since then the united states has become chinas secondlargest 
trading partner after japan with 1988 trade projected at more than 
135 billion more than 50000 chinese will travel to the united 
states in 1988 lord told the seminar thursday and about 300000 
americans will visit china 
hundreds of cultural and scientific exchanges have taken place in 
addition to regular visits by senior government officials 
